-- Czech Stocks: Komercni Banka, Erste Bank, Kit Digital Are Active
-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 2012-07-03T15:16:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/czech-stocks-komercni-banka-erste-bank-kit-digital-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
rose for a third day, advancing 0.1 percent to 912.70 by the
close in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Komercni Banka  AS (KOMB CP), the Czech unit of Societe
Generale SA, advanced for a sixth day, adding 0.1 percent to
3,582 koruna. European stocks advanced on expectations that
central banks in  Europe  and  China  will ease monetary policy to
spur economic growth.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   of Austria gained 1.1 percent
to 396.6 koruna, the highest level since May 11.  Kit Digital Inc. (KITD)  , a maker of online-video
software, fell a second day, declining 1.4 percent to 88 koruna.
The company “expects to book a loss” on its sale of a content
business to Netherlands-based Content Solutions International NV
for $18.8 million, Kit said in a statement late yesterday. The
size of the loss depends on accounting and calculations that
aren’t currently complete, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
